NEWSMAKERS 
George Hughes has been named vice president of Newport Pacific Construction, 
Newport Beach. He will be responsible for evaluating, bidding and administering 
the more than $250 million in construction projects the company has in planning 
and construction phases. Previously, Hughes was manager of operations. Before 
that, he worked for John Bates Associates, Architecture &amp; Land Planning, 
and was director of construction for Berger Construction Co. 
